OL,5, A union representing Rolls Royce       
OL,6, workers has rejected the offer of a    
OL,7, #2,000 one-off payment offered by the  
OL,8, firm to help staff with the rising cost
OL,9, of living.                             
OL,11,FOf the 14,000 staff at Rolls Royce who 
OL,12,Fwere eligible for the payment, 11,000  
OL,13,Fmembers are unionised.                 
OL,15,FThe payment was intended for junior    
OL,16,Fmanagement and shop floor staff.       
OL,18,FUnite said the offer "falls far short  
OL,19,Fof the real cost of living challenges  
OL,20,Fwhich our members are experiencing."   
